27 SECTION 3.3. Article 56A of Chapter 58 of the General Statutes is amended by
28 adding a new section to read:
29 "§ 58-56A-55. Health benefit plan requirements applicable.
30 (a) All requirements relating to the coverage of prescription drugs and pharmacy services
31 under this Chapter that apply to health benefit plans are applicable to pharmacy benefits managers
32 in the same way they are applicable to an insurer.
33 (b) Article 63 of this Chapter, Unfair Trade Practices, is applicable to a pharmacy benefits
34 manager in the same manner as it is applicable to an insurer."
35 SECTION 3.4. G.S. 58-56A-21 reads as rewritten:
36 "§ 58-56A-21. Claims data provided to health benefit plan.Duties owed to contracted
37 insurers.
38 (a) Fiduciary Duty. – A pharmacy benefits manager has a fiduciary duty to act in good
39 faith and fair dealing in the performance of all of its contractual duties, including all of the
40 following:
41 (1) Controlling costs.
42 (2) Acting in the best interest of the insurers and health benefit plans offered by
43 the insurers with which the pharmacy benefits manager has a contract.
44 (3) Acting with prudence and passing through any rebates or discounts the
45 pharmacy benefits manager received related to covered benefits bought and
46 paid for with the contracted insurer's assets or funds.
47 (4) Avoiding self-dealing and conflicts of interest.
48 (b) Claims Data Requests. – Upon the request of an insurer offering a health benefit plan
49 that contracts with a pharmacy benefits manager, the pharmacy benefits manager shall provide
50 the insurer with claims data that reflects the total amount the insurer paid to the pharmacy benefits
51 manager under the health benefit plan for a specified outpatient prescription drug, including the
Senate Bill 479-Fifth Edition Page 9

