13 in this State in the same manner as it applies to an insurer."
14 SECTION 4.2. G.S. 58-56A-15 reads as rewritten:
15 "§ 58-56A-15. Pharmacy benefits manager networks.
16 (a) A pharmacy benefits manager shall not deny the right to any properly licensed
17 pharmacist or pharmacy to participate in a retail pharmacy network on the same terms and
18 conditions of other similarly situated participants in the network.
19 (b) A pharmacist or pharmacy that is a member of a pharmacy service administrative
20 organization that enters into a contract with a health benefit plan issuer or a pharmacy benefits
21 manager on the pharmacy's behalf is entitled to receive from the pharmacy service administrative
22 organization a copy of the contract provisions applicable to the pharmacy, including each
23 provision relating to the pharmacy's rights and obligations under the contract.
24 (c) Termination of a pharmacy or pharmacist from a pharmacy benefits manager network
25 does not release the pharmacy benefits manager from the obligation to make any payment due to
26 the pharmacy or pharmacist for pharmacist services properly rendered according to the contract.
27 This subsection does not apply in cases of fraud, waste, and abuse.
28 (d) A pharmacy benefits manager pharmacy provider network shall meet or exceed the
29 Medicare Part D program standards for convenient access to network pharmacies under 42 C.F.R.
30 § 423.120."
31 SECTION 4.3. This Part is effective October 1, 2025, and applies to contracts
32 entered into, renewed, or amended on or after that date.
