Page 10 Senate Bill 479-Fifth Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 "§ 90-85.21E. Independent pharmacy and pharmacy desert prescriptions.
2 (a) An independent pharmacy or a pharmacist in a pharmacy desert may decline to fill or
3 refill a prescription if (i) that act would directly result in an unbearable cost to the independent
4 pharmacy or pharmacist in a pharmacy desert or (ii) the independent pharmacy or pharmacist in
5 a pharmacy desert will be or is paid less than the acquisition cost for the covered drug, device, or
6 service, provided that the independent pharmacy or pharmacist in a pharmacy desert meets the
7 requirements of subsection (b) of this section. If the independent pharmacy or pharmacist in a
8 pharmacy desert cannot find a pharmacy to accept the referral without causing harm to the
9 patient, then the independent pharmacy or pharmacist in a pharmacy desert must fill the
10 prescription. An independent pharmacy or pharmacist in a pharmacy desert declining to fill a
11 prescription under this section shall not be a violation of any provision of G.S. 90-85.40.
12 (b) If the independent pharmacy or pharmacist in a pharmacy desert elects to decline to
13 fill or refill a prescription under subsection (a) of this section, then, prior to declining to fill or
14 refill a prescription, the independent pharmacy or pharmacist in a pharmacy desert shall refer the
15 prescription and patient to another pharmacy that is equally convenient for the patient to fill or
16 refill the prescription in the same manner without the patient suffering any harm. The
17 independent pharmacy or pharmacist in a pharmacy desert may refer the prescription to a
18 pharmacy that only provides centralized pharmacy services in this State through the mail or
19 remote medication order processing services subject to the Board's rules if the independent
20 pharmacy or pharmacist in a pharmacy desert makes a determination the provision of
21 pharmaceutical services through the mail does not harm the patient."
22 SECTION 5.2. No later than October 1, 2025, the North Carolina Board of Pharmacy
23 shall adopt rules to implement this Part.
24 SECTION 5.3. Section 5.1 of this Part becomes effective October 1, 2025. The
25 remainder of this Part is effective when it becomes law.
